      • reconnect

        public void reconnect(boolean callFromQueue,
                      boolean shouldHandleIdentify)
               throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        This method is used to start the reconnect of the JDA instance. It is public for access from SessionReconnectQueue extensions.
        Parameters:
        callFromQueue - whether this was in SessionReconnectQueue and got polled
        shouldHandleIdentify - whether SessionReconnectQueue already handled an IDENTIFY rate limit for this session
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException
